          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript contains adhyāya 5 of the seventh aṃśa of a larger work called the Śivarahasya, which is itself part of a work on Tantra called the Rudrayāmalatantra. It is dedicated to the praise of the city of Vārāṇasī (Kāśī) a sacred pilgrimage center for the Hindu deity Śiva.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kāśīmahātma</title>
              <title type="vernacular">काशीमहात्म</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīśivarahasye saptamāṃśe śivagaurīsaṃvāde kāśīmahātme kāśīvāsaniyamavidhikathanaṃ nāmapaṃcāmodhyāyaḥ // (f. 5v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
